text.section:
An environmental covenant shall be perpetual except under the following circumstances:
By its terms, the environmental covenant is limited to a specific duration or is terminated by the occurrence of a specific event;
The environmental covenant is terminated pursuant to KRS 224.80-190;
The environmental covenant is terminated by foreclosure of an interest that has priority over the environmental covenant; or
The environmental covenant is terminated or modified in an eminent domain proceeding and the following conditions exist:
The cabinet is a party to the eminent domain proceeding;
All persons identified in KRS 224.80-190(1) and (2) are given notice of the pendency of the eminent domain proceeding; and
A court of competent jurisdiction determines, after hearing, that the termination or modification of the environmental covenant will not adversely affect human health or the environment.
